# Flask Blog
A simple blog application built using Flask and SQLite. It includes user authentication and CRUD operations for blog posts.

Features
User registration and login.
Create, update, delete, and view blog posts.
Secure password hashing with Werkzeug.
SQLite database integration.
Installation
Prerequisites
Python 3.x installed on your system.
Steps
Clone this repository:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/flask-blog.git
cd flask-blog
Create and activate a virtual environment:

On Windows:
bash
Copy
Edit
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
On macOS/Linux:
bash
Copy
Edit
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install -r requirements.txt
Initialize the database:

bash
Copy
Edit
flask init-db
Run the development server:

bash
Copy
Edit
flask run
Open your browser and visit http://127.0.0.1:5000.

Usage
Access the blog at /.
Register a new account at /auth/register.
Log in at /auth/login.
Create posts at /blog/create.
Edit or delete your posts from the main blog page.
Project Structure
csharp
Copy
Edit
flask-blog/
│
├── flaskr/
│   ├── __init__.py      # Application factory
│   ├── auth.py          # Authentication logic
│   ├── blog.py          # Blog post routes
│   ├── db.py            # Database connection logic
│   ├── templates/       # HTML templates
│   └── static/          # Static files (CSS, JS)
│
├── instance/
│   └── flaskr.sqlite    # SQLite database (created after running init-db)
│
├── tests/               # Unit tests
│
├── requirements.txt     # Python dependencies
├── config.py            # Optional configuration file
└── README.md            # Project documentation
